description: Make this easy zucchini fritters recipe for a healthier addition to your little one's lunch box. Team them with juicy strawberries and crunchy pepitas.
keywords: Snack,Pescatarian,Low saturated fat,Seafood free,Low salt,Tree nut free,Healthier Easier,Low sugar,Sesame free,Zucchini,Halal,High protein,High fibre,Soy free,Vegetarian
name: Zucchini Fritters & Snacks Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Using your hands, squeeze excess moisture from zucchini and onion. Place in a large bowl. Add corn, flour, egg and half the ricotta, then mix well to combine. Season with pepper.

Spray a large frying pan with oil and heat over medium-low heat. Working in batches, spoon 1/4 cupfuls zucchini mixture into pan. Cook for 4 minutes on each side or until golden and cooked through. Repeat with remaining zucchini mixture to make a total of 6 fritters.
Place 3 fritters in each lunch box with strawberries, pepitas and remaining ricotta.
